<content>
        
    
Aug 5 (Reuters) - Susan Hedman, regional administrator for
the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency, at a news conference
in Marshall, Michigan, on the Enbridge Inc (ENB.TO) oil
pipeline rupture and spill:

 * Says expects notice from Enbridge soon on pipe excavation
plan * EPA requires 8 hrs notice for excavation of damaged
Michigan pipe
 (Reporting by Jeffrey Jones)




